item.title: A Multiple Linear Regression Analysis
item.description: I spearheaded an in-depth study investigating the intricate interplay between crime rates and socio-economic factors across 47 U.S. states, employing a comprehensive dataset encompassing 11 variables. The study unearthed diverse patterns in the socio-economic landscape, shedding light on unexpected correlations. Key predictors, including police expenditure, income inequality, educational levels, the number of males aged 14-24, and the unemployment rate of urban males aged 35-39, emerged as pivotal factors in the regression model.
